> > My neighborhood "FLAPS" has Optima redtop "blems"
> on sale for $70 and $90,
> > depending on CCA.  They come with a 90 day
> warranty.
> >
> > Anyone know of any risks associated with buying a
> "blem"?  The price seems
> > good!
> 
> A 90 day warranty is horrible!  Any decent battery
> should have at least a
> 5-year warranty.  I've also heard of Optima having
> some rather draconian
> warranty requirements such as sending the bad
> battery back to the
> manufacturer for "inspection" before they will
> authorize a new battery.
> 
> Optimas are good for special applications where you
> need a sealed battery,
> but for a bus you're better off with a conventional
> Pep Boys group 24
> battery in a marine battery box.  No leakage
> problems with the box, and
> the battery is easily servicable and will be
> repplaced under warranty
> without arguement or hassle.
> 
> George Lyle
